# Container Shorthands

### Flex Flow Shorthand

###### flex-flow property is used to declare both the flex-wrap and flex-direction properties in one line.
> - flex-flow

```sass
/* Set flex-direction = column flex-wrap = wrap */
flex-flow: column wrap;


/* Set flex-direction = row reverse flex-wrap = wrap reverse */
flex-flow: row-reverse wrap-reverse;
```



  # Items Shorthands

### Flex Shorthand

###### The flex property allows you to declare flex-grow, flex-shrink, and flex-basis all in one line.
> - flex

```sass
/* Set flex-grow = 2 flex-shrink = 1 and flex-basis = 150px */
flex: 2 1 150px;

/* Set flex-grow = 2 and flex-basis = 150px */
flex: 2 150px;

/* Set flex-grow = 2 flex-shrink = 1 */
flex: 2 1;
```
